Interface Queue<E>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayQueue, LinkedQueue

    public interface Queue<E>
    contains all methods for a queue
    Author:
    William

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      E dequeue()
      removes an element from the queue and returns it throws a NoSuchElementException if the queue is empty
      void enqueue(E element)
      adds element to the back of the queue throws and IllegalArgumentException if the capacity has been reached
      boolean isEmpty()
      returns whether or not a queue is empty (true if so else false)
      void setCapacity(int capacity)
      sets the capacity of the queue throws an IllegalArgumentException if the capacity to be set to is less than the size of the current queue
